# Async Host Module
#
# Host-side async runtime for interfacing with OS-level async I/O.
# Provides integration with epoll/kqueue/IOCP for efficient async operations.
#
# Features:
#   - OS async I/O integration
#   - Join sets for managing multiple tasks
#   - Waker mechanism for task notification
#   - Unordered future execution
#   - Handle-based resource management
#
# Public API:
#   - use std.async_host.runtime.{HostRuntime}
#   - use std.async_host.future.{HostFuture}
#   - use std.async_host.joinset.{JoinSet}
#   - use std.async_host.waker.{Waker}
#   - use std.async_host.handle.{Handle}
#
# Difference from std.async:
#   - std.async: Pure Simple async (portable, embeddable)
#   - std.async_host: OS integration (better performance, OS-specific)

# All submodules are automatically available.
